Section 1:
1 L.D. 1157
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 762, L.D. 1157, “An Act to Amend the
10 Laws Relating to the State's Background Check Center”
11 Amend the bill in section 3 in subsection 10 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 22 in L.D.) by
12 striking out the following: "a final" and inserting the following: 'a final an initial'
13 Amend the bill in section 18 in subsection 10 in paragraph A in the first line (page 4,
14 line 42 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "deposition" and inserting the following:
15 'disposition'
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment makes 2 corrections to the bill. It clarifies that the definition of
2200 "contingent offer of employment" in the Maine Background Check Center Act requires an
2211 initial background check report and not a final one. It also corrects an error in the bill
2222 relating to background check report content by replacing the word "deposition" with
2233 "disposition."
2244 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2255 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0491(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
